HEADWORD: Starred
<hw>Starred</hw> <pr>(st⟦aum⟧rd)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Star</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Adorned or studded with stars;
bespangled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Influenced in fortune by the stars.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My third comfort,⟦br⟧
<qex>Starred</qex> most unluckily.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Starriness</ent>⟦br⟧
